## Security

### Tailscale Tunnel
All agent communication should route through Tailscale:

1. Agents connect via Tailscale IP (100.64.x.x)
2. Firewall blocks external access to health endpoints
3. Mutual TLS optional for additional security

### Rate Limiting
Implement rate limiting at:
- API Gateway / Load Balancer level
- Next.js middleware (optional)
- Per-agent tracking in telemetry store

### Input Validation
- All payloads validated with Zod
- Strict type checking
- Field-level error messages
- Max string lengths enforced
- Numeric ranges validated

---

## Monitoring

### Health Check Intervals
- Load balancer: `GET /api/health/ready` every 10s
- Agent ping: `POST /api/health/ping` every 30s
- Agent heartbeat: `POST /api/agents/heartbeat` every 30s

### Metrics to Track
- Average response time
- P95/P99 latency
- Tunnel latency distribution
- Agent uptime percentage
- Alert frequency by severity
- Rate limit hits

